tags: $:/tags/rimir/llm-connect/example
example-name: Explain for beginners
example-description: Generate a beginner-friendly explanation as a child tiddler using tiddler-level template precedence
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

!! Explain for beginners

Uses tiddler-level precedence: add `llm-context-template: $:/plugins/rimir/llm-connect/context-templates/with-metadata` as a field on your tiddler, and the resolver picks it up automatically — no `contextTemplate` attribute needed on the widget.

The `with-metadata` template sets `output-target: new-tiddler` with `output-title-template`, `output-tags`, and `output-fields`.

''Settings covered:'' action mode, `output-mode: text`, `output-target: new-tiddler`, `output-title-template`, `output-tags`, `output-fields`, tiddler field precedence

```
<$button>
  Explain for beginners
  <$llm-action
    tiddler=<<currentTiddler>>
    prompt="Explain this topic for someone completely new to TiddlyWiki. Use simple language and concrete examples."
  />
</$button>
```

!!! Setup

Add this field to any tiddler you want to use this pattern with:

|!Field |!Value |
|`llm-context-template` |`$:/plugins/rimir/llm-connect/context-templates/with-metadata` |

!!! Live demo

<$button>
  Explain for beginners
  <$llm-action
    tiddler=<<currentTiddler>>
    promptTemplate="$:/plugins/rimir/llm-connect/prompts/explain"
  />
</$button>
